<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1060198-one-of-my-teaching-colleagues-is">One of my teaching colleagues is considering purchasing this book as a gift for a student who is graduating from eighth grade this year. Is there anything terribly inappropriate for a reader of that age? (The student moved here from Iran two or three years ago. We have &quot;It Ain&#39;t So Awful, Falafel&quot; in our middle school library, but it seems a bit young for this reader.)</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1060198'><a id="like_count_community_question_1060198" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1060198?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F46349.Funny_in_Farsi">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1060198-one-of-my-teaching-colleagues-is">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1060198-one-of-my-teaching-colleagues-is">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4341005-summer-larson"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1373329311i/4341005._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4341005-summer-larson">Summer Larson</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
There is nothing inappropriate in this book. I listened to the audio with my children and was perfectly comfortable. 
</span>
</div>
