  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1883719885" />
    <a title="Belhor Crowley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22189980-belhor-crowley"><img alt="Belhor Crowley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518135215p2/22189980.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1883719885?book_show_action=true">Feb 12, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Belhor Crowley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Belhor Crowley" href="/user/show/22189980-belhor-crowley">Belhor Crowley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22189980-belhor-crowley?shelf=novels">novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1883719885" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11215034947052607344">I think maybe if I wasn&apos;t Iranian myself, or if I was an eight year old, I would have found this book more interesting to read, but since I am both Iranian and pretty damn old (inside more than outside), Mrs. Dumas&apos; normal and mostly boring life (specially the married part) didn&apos;t interest me all that much. I did struggle and kept reading until the end of it though. I&apos;m sure this would have made a best seller 100 years ago, when people knew little about other cultures and things like a mispronou</span>
  <span id="freeText11215034947052607344" style="display:none">I think maybe if I wasn't Iranian myself, or if I was an eight year old, I would have found this book more interesting to read, but since I am both Iranian and pretty damn old (inside more than outside), Mrs. Dumas' normal and mostly boring life (specially the married part) didn't interest me all that much. I did struggle and kept reading until the end of it though. I'm sure this would have made a best seller 100 years ago, when people knew little about other cultures and things like a mispronounced name or misunderstood table manners would have seemed insanely funny or cute. So many five stars though. It's a damn shame! </span>
  <a data-text-id="11215034947052607344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


