<span id="freeTextContainer2296319581103871566">This is a wonderful memoir, at times I laughed at loud, at other times I learned. Sometimes I thought &quot;a version of this happens in my (non-immigrant) family.&quot; Towards the end I thought, &quot;I just love Firoozeh&apos;s father.&quot; Who can resist someone who embraces life with his arms wide open and who does good where he can?</span>
